= RailsCommerce

RailsCommerce is an extension of Ruby on Rails for e-commerce development 

= Versionning

= Prerequisites

== Plugins
* acts_as_state_machine
* acts_as_tree
* globalize
* restful_authentication
* will_paginate
* acts_as_commentable

== Initialize
  ./script/generate authenticated user sessions --include-activation
  
  rake db:migrate
  rake globalize:setup
  rake rails_commerce:migrate
  rake rails_commerce:init_translation

== update routes.rb
  map.activate '/activate/:activation_code', :controller => 'users', :action => 'activate'

== update environment.rb
  require File.join(File.dirname(__FILE__), 'boot')

  require "desert" # <--- Here !!!

  Rails::Initializer.run do |config|

= Controllers

== Example

  class CartController < ApplicationController
    include RailsCommerce::CartController
    before_filter :get_cart
  end

= Helpers

== add in application_helper.rb

  include CategoryHelper
  include ProductHelper
  include CartHelper
  include OrderHelper

= Models

== modify create_users migration

  change generated db/migrate/VERSION_create_users file to :

  class CreateUsers < ActiveRecord::Migration
    def self.up
      create_table :users, :force => true do |t|
        t.string :email,
          :firstname,
          :lastname
        t.string :crypted_password,
          :salt,
          :remember_token,
          :activation_code,
          :limit => 40
        t.datetime :created_at,
          :updated_at,
          :remember_token_expires_at,
          :activated_at
      end
    end

    def self.down
      drop_table :users
    end
  end

